how to install:

git clone git clone git@emacsonrails.org:emacsonrails.git

.emacs file
===========
check .emacs.sample
or 
ln -s ~/.emacs.d/.emacs ~/.emacs



Remote Pair Programming
=======================
We recommend:
Add to ~/.ssh/config

# Where to find the control path, if we have one
Host *
   ControlPath ~/.ssh/master-%r@%h:%p
   ForwardAgent yes
   Compression yes
   ForwardX11 yes

Also, You can replace * with your hostname


How to run emacs multi tty
check: http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/MultiTTYSupport
1. run emacs on server mode:
    M-x server-start
2. create a window on screen: 
    C-a c
3. Run emacsclient
    emacsclient -c
    -t, --tty               Open a new Emacs frame on the current terminal
    -c, --create-frame      Create a new frame instead of trying to
                        use the current Emacs frame
         